objects.name: Strategic Planning
objects.description: Define the desired end state, i.e. the set of required conditions that defines achievement of all objectives.

objects.name: Objective Planning
objects.description:
Set clearly defined, measurable, and achievable objectives. Achieving objectives ties execution of tactical tasks to reaching the desired end state. There are four primary considerations:
- Each desired effect should link directly to one or more objectives
- The effect should be measurable
- The objective statement should not specify the way and means of accomplishment
- The effect should be distinguishable from the objective it supports as a condition for success, not as another objective or task.

objects.name: Develop People
objects.description: Develop online and offline users and agents, including automated personas

objects.name: Develop Networks
objects.description: Develop online and offline communities and transmission methods and cultivate assets and unwitting agents

objects.name: Microtargeting
objects.description: Target very specific populations of people

objects.name: Develop Content
objects.description: Create and acquire content used in incident

objects.name: Channel Selection
objects.description: Set up specific delivery, amplification and manipulation channels for incident, including channels to attack. Each channel serves as an atomic surface (test bed) location/site for adversary to hide/conceal the work/content that goes into setting up for this channel and/or other specific platforms. Contributes to building out a connected ecosystem where this channel can operate as part of a whole campaign/incident

objects.name: Pump Priming
objects.description: Release content on a targetted small scale, prior to general release, including releasing seed narratives

objects.name: Exposure
objects.description: Release content to general public or push to larger population

objects.name: Persistence
objects.description: Keep incident 'alive', beyond the incident creators' efforts

objects.name: Measure Effectiveness
objects.description: Measure effectiveness of incident, for use in planning future events
